### Color Usage Rules

**Dark sections** (hero, trust bar, bottom CTA, footer): `--teal-700` background, `--mint-500` for headline text, `rgba(255,255,255,0.5)` for body text, white for primary CTAs.

**Light sections** (features, why, pricing): alternate between `--neutral-50` and `--neutral-75` for background. `--neutral-900` for headings, `--neutral-600` for body text. `--teal-700` for primary buttons.

**Card surfaces**: `--white` on `--neutral-50` background. No visible borders. Separation through subtle shadow only.

**One accent color only.** There is no gold, no second green, no blue. Everything is mint + teal + warm neutral. The workshop-side buttons that were previously gold/tan become `--teal-700` (same as driver-side). Differentiation between audiences happens through copy and layout, never through color.

