## 4. Spacing & Layout

### Section Spacing

```css
:root {
  --section-padding: clamp(80px, 10vw, 140px);
  --content-max: 1160px;
  --text-max: 520px;        /* Max-width for body text blocks */
}
```

Every major section (hero, feature, why, pricing, CTA) has `var(--section-padding)` top and bottom. On a 1440px screen that's 140px — about 9% of the viewport. This is the single most important spatial decision. Do not reduce it.

### Content Grid

```
Max content width:     1160px, centered
Feature section grid:  2 columns, 50/50, 80px gap
Hero grid:            2 columns, 55/45, 80px gap
Pricing cards:         2 columns, max 880px total, 24px gap
```

### Section Background Alternation

```
Hero:          --teal-700 (dark)
Trust bar:     --teal-900 (darker)
Feature 1:     --neutral-50 (light)
Feature 2:     --neutral-75 (slightly darker light)
Feature 3:     --neutral-50 (light)
Why Autoceny:  --white
Pricing:       --neutral-50 (light)
Bottom CTA:    --teal-700 (dark)
Footer:        --teal-900 (darker)
```

This creates a clear rhythm: dark → dark → light → light → light → white → light → dark → dark. The alternation between `--neutral-50` and `--neutral-75` is extremely subtle (~3% difference) — just enough to distinguish sections without hard breaks.

